5|$|In 1931, Eichelberger {{was sent}} to West Point as its adjutant. He was {{promoted}} to lieutenant colonel on 1 August 1934. In April 1935, he became Secretary of the War Department General Staff, working for the Chief of Staff of the United States Army, General <b>Douglas</b> <b>MacArthur.</b> Eichelberger transferred back to the infantry in July 1937, although he remained Secretary of the War Department General Staff until October 1938, in the rank of colonel from 1 August.|$|E
